  "title" : "Get CameraX final resolution",
  "body" : "<p>Just created a camera preview in Android with CameraX with the following configuration:</p>\n\n<pre><code>    PreviewConfig previewConfig = new PreviewConfig.Builder()\n            .setLensFacing(CameraX.LensFacing.FRONT)\n            .setTargetResolution(new Size(720, 720))\n            .build();\n    Preview preview = new Preview(previewConfig);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Now, the problem is that such target resolution may not be available, in which case the preview will choose a resolution closed to the requested one. What I'm asking here is a way to know which resolution has effectively be chosen by the preview.</p>\n\n<p>Thanks in advance!</p>\n"
}